init_text: Following World War III, all the nations of the world agreed to 50 years of strict isolation from one another in order to prevent additional conflicts. 50 years later, the United States comes out of exile, only to learn that no one else went into isolation.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The story follows a group of soldiers as they try to find out what happened to the other nations of the world.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: They formed a world government and are now at war with the United States.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: are now trying to take over the United States.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The others, however, were not so sure.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The soldiers were all former prisoners of war and were still very bitter about the treatment they received while in captivity.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "We'll show them what we think of their world government."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The group of soldiers then went to the World Capital and blew it up.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: This started a war between the United States and the World Government.
